---
# `min` is the enforced CI gate: real correctness problems (unresolvable
# modules/collections, broken schema, syntax errors) are fatal. It
# deliberately does NOT enforce the `basic` profile's style rules yet --
# doing so today would require touching ~40 pre-existing files across nearly
# every role for var-naming (94 findings, e.g. base_dir/container_name
# without a role prefix -- the established convention across every
# docker-compose role in this repo), role-name[path] (37 findings, e.g.
# `helper/ssh` -- how every role in roles/helper/ is referenced everywhere),
# and yaml formatting (~60 findings), none of which this pets-to-cattle
# overhaul touched. Ratchet this up to `basic` as those get cleaned up.
profile: min

exclude_paths:
  - .cache/
